<D>__{written by andrew niccol}
<T>__{fade up:}
<A>__{close up on the face of yuri orlov. late thirties, maybe the wrong side of forty, cigarette dangling from his fingers, wearing a conservative suit and tie. black smoke wafts in front of his face. he speaks matter of factly, directly into camera.}
<C>__{yuri}
<D>__{there are over 550 million firearms in worldwide circulation. that's one firearm for every twelve people on the planet. the only question is...}
<P>__{(taking a draft and stubbing out the cigarette)}
<D>__{...how do we arm the other eleven?}
<A>__{the camera zooms away from his face, revealing: yuri alone on a battlefield surrounded by the charred carcasses of armored military vehicles and other equipment, discarded weapons and ammunition, desert floor stained with what appears to be blood. the faint sound of gunfire, some distance away, carries to us on the wind.}
